.TH KFLC 1 "May 2026" "KFL_Stack 0.4.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kflc \- compiler for the KFL programming language
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kflc
.RI [ options ]
.I input.kfl
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBkflc\fR parses a KFL source file (\fI.kfl\fR) and emits a C++
intermediate source which is then compiled by the system C++ toolchain
into a native executable. KFL is a scope-oriented language with arena
allocation, own/borrow/ptr ownership qualifiers, and built-in bindings
for the K26 numerical library suite.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -o \fIfile\fR
Write the produced binary to \fIfile\fR. Default is derived from the
input filename.
.TP
.B -c
Compile only; do not link. Produces an object file.
.TP
.B --dump
Dump the parsed AST to standard output. Useful for debugging.
.TP
.B --emit
Emit the generated C++ source to standard output without compiling.
.TP
.B --check
Type-check the input without emitting code.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KFLC_BUILTINS_PATH
Colon-separated list of directories searched for
.I .kflbi
builtin manifests. Defaults to
.I /usr/share/kflc/builtins
when unset.
.TP
.B KFLC_LDLIBS
Link libraries passed to the C++ toolchain. Defaults to
.IR -lm .
A program that uses a K26 library must add the matching flags, for
example
.I "-lk26plot -lk26compute -lk26m3d -lcairo -lm"
for a plotting program.
.TP
.B KFLC_CFLAGS
Compile flags passed to the C++ toolchain. Defaults to
.IR "-O2 -g -std=c++11 -Wno-format-truncation" .
.TP
.B CXX
C++ compiler to invoke. Defaults to
.IR c++ .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/kflc/builtins/*.kflbi
Builtin manifests installed by the
.B libk26<name>-dev
packages; kflc reads these to learn which K26 library bindings are
available.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/kflc/GRAMMAR.md
Full KFL grammar reference.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/kflc/examples/
Annotated example programs covering language features and the astro
library suite.
.SH EXAMPLES
Build and run a compute program (standard library only):
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ kflc compute_kepler.kfl -o kepler
$ ./kepler
.fi
.RE
.PP
Build a plotting program; it writes a PNG and an SVG per figure:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ KFLC_LDLIBS="-lk26plot -lk26compute -lk26m3d -lcairo -lm" \\
    kflc orbital_mechanics.kfl -o orbital
$ ./orbital
.fi
.RE
.PP
Build a simulation program; it prints its observations:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ KFLC_LDLIBS="-lk26astro_rt -lk26astro_grav -lk26astro_conics \\
    -lk26astro_atmos -lk26astro_vehicle -lk26astro_body \\
    -lk26astro_ephem -lk26astro_core -lk26astro_quad -lk26astro_ode \\
    -lk26astro_geomag -lk26compute -lk26tick -lk26m3d -lgfortran -lm" \\
    kflc astro_apophis_2029.kfl -o apophis
$ ./apophis
.fi
.RE
.PP
Inspect the emitted C++:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ kflc --emit foo.kfl | head -50
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
The KFL grammar reference at
.IR /usr/share/doc/kflc/GRAMMAR.md ,
example programs at
.IR /usr/share/doc/kflc/examples/ .
